<br>
DS is 43 points (level+2)<br>
High HP (about 51 earth)<br>
Aggro Proc that really keeps mob on the pet and not you.<br>
<br>
I was able to cast Sirroco and then sit down, mob stayed right on pet. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 6:21:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1666.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dyzil's Deafening Decoy</span><hr size=1> It is a great pet, kinda like a 51 earth pet without root and has a very nice damage shield. Unfortunately at my level, the pet is good only for killing greenies and power leveling someone under 50. <p><p><a
