<br>
It is singularly the most efficient pet at taunting mobs off of PCs.<br>
<br>
If you have a cleric friend, you can send the pet into a room filled with blue mobs.  Dyzil AE taunt pulls all the mobs onto him,  Cleric chainheals the pet (pet has low HP so be sure to have healer stay on top of the heals) and the mobs destroy themselves on his DS.  Cleric need not worry as heal assist aggro isnt transferred through pets.  As the mage, you just stand there and watch until all mobs down to low HP then go stand next to your pet and cast Scintillation.<br>
<br>
Fun Fun Fun.<br>
<br>
I also treat this pet as the 'diversion' pet, for when I want to distract a bunch fo mobs for a bit.  For example, to get through SG and the see-invis Seahorses, I jump into the water with a Dyzil pet, pull the seahorses, and transfer the aggro to the pet.  Quite often you'll see the mobs making a beeline for you and 'bam' they change direction and ehad for pet.  Of course, the seahorses make short work of him, but by the time pet goes down, Im on the other side of the waterfall on dry ground putting invis up.  Seahorses can only watch and be mad, as they cant get out of the water.<br>
<br>
Erun<br>
60 Mage<br>
